\b 36- CONNECTION OF LIGHT WITH CONSCIOUSNESS AND THE SPIRITUAL WORLD\b0\par
\par
The relationship between visible light and invisible light (such as X-rays, gamma rays) can have a deep meaning not only on a physical plane, but also in metaphysical and symbolic meanings. From a scientific perspective, these types of light belong to different parts of the electromagnetic spectrum and have different energy levels. However, when these lights are considered in a broader context, they have a deep potential to create metaphors related to consciousness and the spiritual world.\par
