\par
The quantum uncertainty of photons can be considered as a deep metaphor symbolizing the unlimited potential of the human soul. In quantum physics, photons, namely light particles, are entities subject to the uncertainty principle, acting as both waves and particles. This uncertainty indicates that a photon can contain multiple possibilities at the same time and that a result becomes clear only when a measurement is made. Similarly, the concept of the unlimited potential of the soul expresses the capacity of a person's soul to reach infinite levels of possibility and consciousness despite having a limited physical existence.\par
